 |elevation_ft= |postal_code_type = ZIP code |postal_code = 55401, 55402, 55403, 55404, 55415, 55487 |area_code = [[area code 612|612]] |website = |footnotes = |demographics = <!-- enter template using {{US Census tract embedded}} --> }} <!-- Infobox ends --> {{USCensusPop |1980= 3522 |1990= 3789 |2000= 4581 |2010= 5781 }} '''Downtown West''' is an official neighborhood in [[Minneapolis]], part of the larger [[Central, Minneapolis|Central community]]. It is the heart of downtown Minneapolis (and Minneapolis as a whole), containing the bulk of high-rise office buildings in the city, and is what comes to mind when most Minneapolitans think of "downtown". Its boundaries are as follows (going in a clockwise direction): 12th Street to the southwest, 3rd Avenue North, Washington Avenue North, and [[Hennepin Avenue]] to the northwest, the [[Mississippi River]] to the northeast, and Portland Avenue, 5th Street South, and 5th Avenue South to the southeast. It is bordered by the [[North Loop, Minneapolis|North Loop]], [[Nicollet Island/East Bank, Minneapolis|Nicollet Island/East Bank]], [[Downtown East, Minneapolis|Downtown East]], [[Elliot Park, Minneapolis|Elliot Park]], and [[Loring Park, Minneapolis|Loring Park]] neighborhoods. Downtown West is home to most of Minneapolis's most notable buildings like the [[Foshay Tower]] and [[IDS Center]]. Being next to the neighborhood [[Loring Park, Minneapolis|Loring Park]] which has a substantial population of gay people, it is unsurprising that Downtown West has a few gay bars such as [[The Saloon, Minneapolis|The Saloon]]. {{Coord|44.9741|-93.2732|region:US-MN_type:city(4581)_source:GoogleEarth|display=title|notes=<ref>''Downtown West, Minneapolis, MN.'' [[Google Earth]]. Retrieved 2011-03-09.</ref>}}
