[[File:Guilherme Leal Cropped.jpg|thumb|Guilherme Leal]]
'''Guilherme Peirão Leal''' (born 22 February 1950 in [[Santos, São Paulo|Santos]]) is a [[Brazil]]ian billionaire [[entrepreneur]]. He is the co-chairman of the board of directors of, and owns a 25 percent stake in, [[Natura]], Brazil's leading manufacturer and marketer of [[skin care]], [[Sun|solar]] filters, [[cosmetics]], [[perfume]] and [[hair care]] products. According to [[Forbes (magazine)|''Forbes'']], Leal had a fortune worth roughly US$2.1 billion as of 2010.

== Political activity ==
He ran as the [[Green Party (Brazil)|Green Party]] candidate for vice president alongside [[Marina Silva]] in the [[Brazilian presidential election, 2010|2010 Brazilian presidential election]]. Their ticket came in third, with 19,634,663 of the votes (19.33 percent), and carried the [[Brazilian Federal District]].

